class Solution {
    public int findLUSlength(String a, String b) {
        if (a.equals(b)) {
            return -1;
        } else {
            return Math.max(a.length(), b.length());
        }
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution checks if the two input strings are equal. If they are, it returns -1, as there is no uncommon subsequence. If they are not equal, it returns the length of the longer string, which is the longest uncommon subsequence. This approach works because the longest uncommon subsequence between two strings is the longer string itself if the strings are not equal.

